				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm Kiting, Please help :(<a name="1843"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 28 02 6:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>    My method is pretty easy I think.
<br />

<br />
 Pick a mob and run him around until I have as many as I need to give it a good beating in less than 60 seconds of charm time.
<br />

<br />
Easier with level 49 selos that lasts 2.5 mins. and clicky lev from the SS boots. (optional)
<br />

<br />
Charm mob spam F8 until I target closest mob, hit attack button and stay as close as safely possible to watch pet life. Too much distance seems to mess with my pet life bar. 
<br />

<br />
When he's almost dead I click on Invis song to break charm, and Chant DoT the pet to death.
<br />

<br />
Repeat!<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
With the additional DoT songs it should be even easier. The more mobs you can get to do dmg on your pet the better, but I tend to stick with 3 to 5 mobs so I don't have to run from the extras that my pet won't taunt off me.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes with mobs that run or fear easy I will charm mob and have it help me fear kite the 2nd mob. Very fun as well.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
