				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm Kiting, Please help :(<a name="1846"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 28 02 8:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I normally have a hotkey made that says /pet report health
<br />

<br />
That normally gives me a better indication of the exact health of me pet while charm/swarm kiting.
<br />

<br />
As for swarm kiting itself, might i suggest sticking to two mobs first and then expanding to three, four, x mobs as you get more proficient<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
The trick to swarm kiting is to find social mobs and get them to beat up on your pet for the duration of charm. Once charm breaks, hopefully your pet will be at a low enough health level for you to chant it down (all the time running around with the all the mobs behind yous). Once its dead, just pick the next mob to charm and sic on his buddies).
<br />

<br />
There are lots of places to practice swarm kiting. look through the hunting guides for locations. However, initially, i'd stick with low blues or greens just to get a feel for it.
<br />

<br />
-Secours-
<br />
</span></td>
