			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm Kiting, Please help :(<a name="2098"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 19 02 6:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Other keys for me (not everyone does it my way)
<br />

<br />
Lock on run.  You are using hotkeys 1-0 keyed to your spell gems (i don't macro, but some like it), or have remapped F1 thu F8 to spell gems and still have your 10 macros, so you can leave your right hand to run the keybad arrows and the mouse. Usually there is enuf room to move right hand to the mouse to target and not turn for a bit, if not, i move left hand to dedicated arrow pad and run mouse with right.
<br />

<br />
I have to use 3rd person view, usually zoomed all the way out and rotated for best advantage for my chosen area. This can be adjusted in the 3rd and 4th mode btw...alt left/right arrow spins it, alt home/end increase decreases elevation, alt up/down arrow zooms in and out. (if turned on. right click/hold mouse does some of this, but i like to do it sometimes on the fly and my hands are usually on the keyboard.
<br />

<br />
Dire wolves hit a little hard at 30, and as you may read in some of the other posts, the charm will stick a little better as you level up.
<br />

<br />
Certainly practice with two, then three then more. 
<br />

<br />
F1 Charm
<br />
F2 BBB
<br />
F3 Fufil's Dot
<br />
F4 Selo's
<br />
F5 Heal
<br />
F6-F8 use imagination
<br />

<br />
` Target self (the old F1), hit twice targets charm
<br />
1 /pet attack
<br />
2 /pet health
<br />
3-0 use imagination
<br />

<br />
Set up above order for what makes sense to you.
<br />

<br />
Play songs with left hand, control movement with right.
<br />

<br />
I always took a hit at that level to aggro the swarm, with the 18 sec charm, its was easier for me than 'target nearest mob', /pet attack, 'target self', 'target self', to get charm back in target window.
<br />

<br />
There is a knack to glancing off the swarm and not getting hit by too many. Down side, you will (not often) get stunned and swarmed. Upside, defense skills keep building.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
