			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm Kiting, Please help :(<a name="2139"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 25 02 3:45 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I generally find a social mob, Walrus's in your 40's are great for this and EW is made for kiting of any sort.  Charm him and send him into one of this buddies, any walrii passing by will jump in and they're so closely packed on the souther edge of the zone that you'll soon have 5 or more in a pack.  I have a hot key set to /pet attack, /target pet so I can just get the pack going... F8 to target the nearest mob that's not my pet, hit my macro and my pet attacks and is still my target for recharming or chanting as the case may be. 
<br />

<br />
You can also use the Tab buffer and the F1 keys if you dont' want to use hotkeys for it, Tab switches between you and your last target and F1 targets you on the first tap and your pet on the second so you can have your pet attack then quickly hit F1 twice to retarget your pet.
<br />

<br />
I like to use a mix of swarm and chant kiting, I get a sizable mob chasing me and then randomly pick mobs from the pack wtih F8 to charm and mix things up a bit, when I get a mob that's real low on health, say 30% or less I toss all three Dot's on it and they usually drop... all three dots over their duration will do quite a number on a walrus.
<br />

<br />
I've got a variation on kiting now that I do with a wizard friend of mine and it's quite productive.  I'll run out into EW, pull  as many mobs as I can find, doesn't matter what tehy are but I like to keep my mob homogenous so all giants, or all walrii or all rhinos/mammoths, etc... I get about 12 of them on me by roaming the zone and throwing dots on them to get them inline behind me and to get good agro, 3 or 4 twists each with the dots works well... you have to get agro firmly on yourself and here's why... once I've got a good dozen say.. Frost Giant Savages on me, all properly dotted, I then run past my wizard parnter... twist in Selo's for him in case he as to run and while I pick off mobs in the pack with AE Dots and the Tuyen's chants... he does little (210) AE nukes on the mob behind me... that's why I need to have good agro, so they don't split off onto him.  we can drop 10 mobs in about 2-3 minutes this way.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><img src="http://www.geetronics.com/liis4.jpg"><hr>
Liis Tenning, Impresario Vah Shir Maestro, Drinal Server - Malevolent Spirits</span></td>
